{"PageNumber":15,"Angle":0,"RotatedAngle":0,"Height":1620,"Width":2880,"OriginHeight":0,"OriginWidth":0,"Elements":[{"Index":0,"Type":"title","Text":"#  RSA Security","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":216,"Y":305},"LeftTop":{"X":216,"Y":185},"RightBottom":{"X":873,"Y":305},"RightTop":{"X":873,"Y":185}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":1,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● The security of the RSA cryptosystem is based on the difficulty of finding $d$, given $e$ and $n$","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":216,"Y":567},"LeftTop":{"X":216,"Y":427},"RightBottom":{"X":2627,"Y":567},"RightTop":{"X":2627,"Y":427}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":2,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● If we knew $\\varphi(n) = (p-1)(q-1)$, it would be easy to compute $d$ from $e$.","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":216,"Y":665},"LeftTop":{"X":216,"Y":589},"RightBottom":{"X":2394,"Y":665},"RightTop":{"X":2394,"Y":589}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":3,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Thus, Bob needs to keep $p$ and $q$ secret (or even destroy all knowledge of them), since anyone who knows the values of $p$ and $q$ immediately knows the value of $\\varphi(n)$","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":216,"Y":893},"LeftTop":{"X":216,"Y":689},"RightBottom":{"X":2719,"Y":893},"RightTop":{"X":2719,"Y":689}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":4,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Anyone who knows the value of $\\varphi(n)$ can compute $d = e^{-1} \\mod \\varphi(n)$, using the extended Euclidean algorithm","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":216,"Y":1050},"LeftTop":{"X":216,"Y":909},"RightBottom":{"X":2731,"Y":1050},"RightTop":{"X":2731,"Y":909}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":5,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Thus, the security of the RSA cryptosystem is closely tied to factoring $n$, which would reveal the values of $p$ and $q$","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":216,"Y":1215},"LeftTop":{"X":216,"Y":1068},"RightBottom":{"X":2728,"Y":1215},"RightTop":{"X":2728,"Y":1068}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":6,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Fortunately, since this problem has shown itself to be hard to solve, we can continue to rely on the security of the RSA cryptosystem, provided we use a large enough modulus","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":216,"Y":1442},"LeftTop":{"X":216,"Y":1235},"RightBottom":{"X":2659,"Y":1442},"RightTop":{"X":2659,"Y":1235}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""}]}